                            <comment id="23620" author="adilger" created="Thu, 1 Dec 2011 21:08:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The link count bugs are due to glibc not knowing the maximum link count for Lustre. I&apos;ve submitted a patch upstream for this and it will be fixed in some upcoming release. &lt;br/&gt;
The mtime after write  is more interesting and should be working properly. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23619" author="sarah" created="Thu, 1 Dec 2011 21:02:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;duplicate with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-380&quot; title=&quot;POSIX: write.15: time stamps incorrect: mtime, ctime were not updated&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-380&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-380&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23618" author="sarah" created="Thu, 1 Dec 2011 21:01:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your explanation, then I will make this duplicate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23617" author="yujian" created="Thu, 1 Dec 2011 20:58:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Sarah,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The unlink.6 and write.15 failures are &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-380&quot; title=&quot;POSIX: write.15: time stamps incorrect: mtime, ctime were not updated&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-380&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-380&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
The link.15, mkdir.12 and rename.35 failures are false failures, because Lustre does not have a maximum number of subdirectories, and so I did not file a Jira ticket for them before.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
